Die grösste Bergkette der Welt.


{ INDEPTH #indepth

  = International Deep Profiling of Tibet and the Himalaya.

  INDEPTH Forschungen zeigten eine Schicht wässriger Flüssigkeit unter dem tibetischen Plateau.

}

{ Das Plateaurätsel #plateauraetsel

 "
  The problem of the uplift of large plateau areas is one which has puzzled students of the
  Earth's crust for a very long time. ~what mechanism~ would cause a large volumen of low standing continents to rise rapidly a mile in the air?
  Furthermore, evidence from gravity surveys suggests that the rocks underlying the Colorade plateau are in isostatic balance, that is,
  this large area is ~floating at its correct elevation~ in view of its mass and density. Recent seismic evidence confirms this, in that
  the depth to the [→ Wissenschaft/Geologie/Moho[Moho]] discontinuity under the Colorado plateau is approximately 10 kilometers greater
  than over most of continental North America …
  -
  We have then a double-ended mystery, for the Coloradoplateau seems to have grown downward at the same time that its emerged part rose upward.
 " [George C. Kennedy: The Origin of Continents, Mountain Ranges and Ocean Basins, American Scientist, Vol 47, Dez 1959, pp 493-495]

}
{ Erdachsenverschiebung

  Die grosse Masse des tibetanischen Plateaus und des Himalayas verursachte die → Wissenschaft/Hydroplattentheorie/Erdachsenverschiebung und
  indirekt den → Wissenschaft/Geologie/Neunzig-Grad-Ost-Rücken südlich des Himalayas/tibetanischen Plateaus.

}
